&lt;p&gt;White, porous, pliable and absorbable collagen wound dressing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common uses:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="list-style-type: disc;"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extraction socket graft coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hemostasis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; molar extractions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Soft tissue repair.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free-gingival graft donor sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Features and benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="list-style-type: disc;"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly purified Type I bovine collagen.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High density for added resilience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Easily trimmed according to clinical needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully absorbable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can easily be shaped by hand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Individually packaged and sterile.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

Suture needles are made from Series 300 Stainless Steel, the ideal alloy for dental sutures. This alloy allows a very fine point geometry, stays sharp throughout the suturing procedure and is less likely to bend and more resistant to breakage. In addition, the needles have a&nbsp;high-polished finish for a smoother penetration.
&nbsp;
For Perma Sharp&reg; Sutures Chart&nbsp;along with additional information,&nbsp;click here.

Composed of 80% carbonate phosphate based mineral with a carbonate apatite structure combined with 20% Type I Achilles bovine tendon collagen. This mineral is physically and chemically comparable to the mineralized matrix of human bone, which makes it an excellent choice for socket preservation. No membrane needed in most cases. &nbsp;
Intended for use in dental surgery including:
&bull; Augmentation or reconstructive treatment of the alveolar ridge.&bull; Filling of infrabony periodontal defects.&bull; Filling of defects after root resection, apicoectomy, and cystectomy.&bull; Filling of extraction sockets to enhance preservation of alveolar ridge.&bull; Elevation of the maxillary sinus floor.&bull; Filling of periodontal defects in conjunction with GTR. &bull; Filling of peri-implant defects in conjunction with GBR.
